description: Field-level encryption, rotation, and related key management in this repo
---

# Field-level encryption (prisma-field-encryption)

Annotations in app/prisma/schema.prisma mark encrypted and hashed fields, e.g.
- /// @encrypted on columns like User.email, AccountRegister.name, RegisterEntry.description, Reoccurrence.description
- @encryption:hash(...) on normalized hash columns (e.g., plaidIdHash, emailHash, walletAddressHash)

Generated migrators
- app/prisma/reencrypt/* and microservice/prisma/reencrypt/* contain generated migrators and an index.ts with migrate() exported
- Used for re-encrypting records when rotating keys or after restoring data from another environment

Runtime keys
- DB_ENCRYPTION_KEY and optional DB_DECRYPTION_KEY_* variables provided via K8S secrets (SECRET_DB in templates)
- The application’s Prisma client loads prisma-field-encryption extension with the appropriate keys (see server/clients/prismaClient.ts)

# Rotation workflows

Staging nightly rotation
- .deploy/key-rotation-cronjob.template.yaml runs the microservice :keyrotate image
- Script microservice/scripts/k8s-rotate-db-key.sh:
  - Patches the secret containing encryption material
  - Restarts Deployments so new keys take effect
  - Calls microservice /migrate endpoint to invoke generated re-encrypt migrators
- RBAC in .deploy/key-rotation-rbac.template.yaml grants the CronJob permissions to update the secret and patch deployments

Post-restore local plan
- docs/post-restore-encryption-plan.md describes enhancing scripts/reset-encrypted-users-after-restore.ts to:
  - Use generated reencrypt/migrate when a source env key is present (decrypt with source, encrypt with local)
  - Otherwise, overwrite sensitive fields with safe placeholders across User, AccountRegister, RegisterEntry, Reoccurrence, and null Plaid columns

# Other keys and crypto utilities

- RSA keypairs persisted in table Rsa; app/server/services/RsaService.ts manages key usage
- JWT: app/server/services/JwtService.ts with rotateUserJwtKey helper (server/lib/rotateUserJwtKey.ts)
- Hashing: app/server/services/HashService.ts and tests; emailHash and plaidIdHash columns derived via encryption annotations
- Plaid access tokens and IDs are encrypted and hashed at rest

# Safety notes

- Never log raw encrypted payloads or secrets
- Keep SECRET_DB limited to field-encryption materials; DATABASE_URL lives in dedicated secrets
- Update env schema validation when adding/changing key variables
- When introducing new encrypted fields, annotate Prisma schema and regenerate reencrypt code (pnpm --filter dineros-app exec prisma generate)
